  "prompt": "What are the lyrics to the Korean happy birthday song?",
  "response": "The standard Korean \"Happy Birthday\" song is based on the melody of the English version, but with different lyrics. Here are the lyrics:\n\n**Hangul (Korean Script):**\n\n\uc0dd\uc77c \ucd95\ud558\ud569\ub2c8\ub2e4 (saeng-il chuk-ha-ham-ni-da)\n\uc0dd\uc77c \ucd95\ud558\ud569\ub2c8\ub2e4 (saeng-il chuk-ha-ham-ni-da)\n\uc0ac\ub791\ud558\ub294 [Name] \uc528 (sa-rang-ha-neun [Name] ssi)\n\uc0dd\uc77c \ucd95\ud558\ud569\ub2c8\ub2e4 (saeng-il chuk-ha-ham-ni-da)\n\n**Romanization (Easier to Read):**\n\nSaeng-il chuk-ha-ham-ni-da\nSaeng-il chuk-ha-ham-ni-da\nSa-rang-ha-neun [Name] ssi\nSaeng-il chuk-ha-ham-ni-da\n\n**English Translation:**\n\nHappy birthday to you\nHappy birthday to you\nDear [Name]\nHappy birthday to you\n\n**Explanation of the Parts:**\n\n*   **\uc0dd\uc77c (saeng-il):** Birthday\n*   **\ucd95\ud558\ud569\ub2c8\ub2e4 (chuk-ha-ham-ni-da):** Congratulations / I congratulate you (formal)\n*   **\uc0ac\ub791\ud558\ub294 (sa-rang-ha-neun):** Beloved / Dear\n*   **[Name]:** Replace this with the person's name.\n*   **\uc528 (ssi):** A polite title used to address someone (similar to \"Mr.\" or \"Ms.\").\n\n**How to Sing:**\n\nSing it to the same tune as the English \"Happy Birthday.\"  Replace \"[Name]\" with the person's name you are celebrating.\n\n**Important Notes:**\n\n*   The formal ending \"\ud569\ub2c8\ub2e4 (ham-ni-da)\" is generally used in most situations, especially when singing in a group or when the person being celebrated is older than you or of higher status.\n*   You might hear variations or additions, but this is the standard and most common version.\n*   Sometimes people will add \"\uc0dd\uc77c \ucd95\ud558\ud574\uc694 (saeng-il chuk-ha-hae-yo)\" after the standard verse.  This is a slightly less formal way of saying \"Happy Birthday.\"",
